KAIRUKI Hospital has offered free medical checkup for over 200 children of Bima Mkononi customers. The hospital had joined hands with MILVIK Tanzania, the provider of Bima Mkononi, in partnership with Tigo Tanzania and Resolution, over the weekend. Kairuki’s Head of Marketing and Communications Ms Arafa Juba said the exercise was conducted to under-16 year old children. Ms Juba advised parents to cultivate a culture of checking their children health regularly to record their kids’ health status. The medical checkup was on optical, diabetes and counseling. MILVIK Tanzania Trainee Assistant Mr Rajabu Salehe said the aim was to raise awareness on importance of Tigo mobile insurance. The free health checkup was accompanied by visit to children wards where various gifts, such as diapers, toothbrushes, and toys, were donated.